Program: Free Thinking
Title: Rebecca Solnit, Wonder Woman, Submarine Films
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04tcc1q
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 10 Dec 2014
American author Rebecca Solnit discusses the impact of "mansplaining" which she explores in her book Men Explain Things To Me. Matthew Sweet looks at the image of Wonder Woman with comic artist Steve Marchant and Jill Lepore, author of The Secret History of Wonder Woman. New Generation Thinker Dr Will Abberley discusses the literary traditions followed by submarine films from Jude Law's new cinema release The Black Sea to Das Boot and The Hunt for Red October. Producer: Zahid Warley You can download this programme by searching in the Arts and Ideas podcasts for the broadcast date. Show less